The paper focuses on the digital library research community and applies social network analysis to co-authorship networks. This falls under the domain of digital libraries, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also analyzes the impact of individual authors in the network, which relates to social network analysis (cs.SOC). Additionally, the paper discusses international participation in digital library conferences, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) if it involves issues related to privacy and security. Finally, the paper could also be classified under the sub-category of information science (cs.SI) as it deals with the organization and dissemination of information.
